# Answers (Optimized Solutions)
---

## Answer 1 — Users Logged In 3 Consecutive Days
WITH cte AS (
SELECT user_id,
       login_date,
       LAG(login_date,1) OVER(
           PARTITION BY user_id
           ORDER BY login_date
       ) AS prev1,
       LAG(login_date,2) OVER(
           PARTITION BY user_id
           ORDER BY login_date
       ) AS prev2
FROM Logins
)
SELECT DISTINCT user_id
FROM cte
WHERE DATEDIFF(login_date, prev1) = 1
  AND DATEDIFF(prev1, prev2) = 1;
```
---

## Answer 2 — Longest Consecutive Order Streak
WITH numbered AS (
SELECT customer_id,
       order_date,
       ROW_NUMBER() OVER(
           PARTITION BY customer_id
           ORDER BY order_date
       ) rn
FROM Orders
),
grp AS (
SELECT customer_id,
       order_date,
       DATE_SUB(order_date, INTERVAL rn DAY) grp_key
FROM numbered
)
SELECT customer_id,
       COUNT(*) AS longest_streak
FROM grp
GROUP BY customer_id, grp_key;
```

### Note

To get max streak only, wrap with another aggregation using `MAX()`.

